cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Autonomous Basis Injection: Frozen-Module Domain Transfer Across LLM Architectures"
message: "If you use ABI or build on these results, please cite this repository."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Yoder
    given-names: Sam
repository-code: "https://github.com/Yoder23/abi"
license: "Apache-2.0"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-05-18"
abstract: >
  ABI (Autonomous Basis Injection) is a method for frozen-module domain transfer
  across LLM architectures. A domain module trained on one model backbone can be
  migrated to a second, independently initialized model by calibrating only
  interface projections — the backbone weights in both models remain entirely
  frozen. Results are verified via the Non-Inferiority Benchmark (NIB) across
  decoder-only and encoder-decoder architectures, 4 model families, and
  117M–774M parameter scale.
keywords:
  - large-language-models
  - domain-adaptation
  - knowledge-transfer
  - frozen-modules
  - non-inferiority-benchmark
  - pytorch
  - transformers
